# Testing — {{SolutionName}}

## Layers

- **Unit** (`tests/{{SolutionName}}.Modules.{Name}.Tests.Unit/`) — xunit + NSubstitute. Mock `I{Entity}Repository` and unit-test command/query handlers. **Never mock the DbContext.**
- **Integration** (`tests/{{SolutionName}}.Modules.{Name}.Tests.Integration/`) — xunit + `Testcontainers.PostgreSql`. Real Postgres 17 container, real `DbContext`, exercise the repository through its public API. Use `IClassFixture<{Name}DbFixture>` to share a container per test class.

## Conventions

- Test name: `{Method}_{Scenario}_{ExpectedResult}` (e.g. `Handle_WhenFooNotFound_ReturnsFailure`).
- Use `Guid.CreateVersion7()` in tests — never `Guid.NewGuid()`.
- Always `fixture.Db.ChangeTracker.Clear()` between operations in integration tests to avoid stale tracking state.

## Running

```bash
dotnet test                                                                        # all
dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~{{SolutionName}}.Modules.{Name}.Tests.Unit" # one project
dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Handle_WhenFooNotFound"                   # one test
```

Integration tests need Docker running (Testcontainers).
